  "is_vocab": false,
  "stimulus_html": "<p>Simple sugars undergo reaction with phenylhydrazine, PhNH–NH<sub>2</sub>, to yield crystalline derivatives called <i>osazones.</i> The reaction is a bit complex, however, as shown by the fact that glucose and fructose yield the same osazone.</p>\n<img class=\"scaled-down\" src=\"https://exercises.openstax.org/rails/active_storage/blobs/proxy/eyJfcmFpbHMiOnsibWVzc2FnZSI6IkJBaHBBcEFaIiwiZXhwIjpudWxsLCJwdXIiOiJibG9iX2lkIn19--08af525788811a8a323aaf62d70ea024a40240d4/OChem_25_EC_019.jpg\" alt=\"D-Glucose and D-fructose when treated with excess phenyl hydrazine form the same osazone  with  phenhydrazones at C 1 and C 2\">",
  "questions": [
    {
      "id": 358831,
      "is_answer_order_important": false,
      "stimulus_html": "",
      "stem_html": "Draw the structure of a third sugar that yields the same osazone as glucose and fructose.",
      "answers": [],
      "hints": [],
      "formats": [
        "free-response"
      ],
      "combo_choices": []
    },
    {
      "id": 358832,
      "is_answer_order_important": false,
      "stimulus_html": "",
      "stem_html": "Using glucose as the example, the first step in osazone formation is reaction of the sugar with phenylhydrazine to yield an imine called a <i>phenylhydrazone.</i> Draw the structure of the product.",
      "answers": [],
      "hints": [],
      "formats": [
        "free-response"
      ],
      "combo_choices": []
    },
    {
      "id": 358833,
      "is_answer_order_important": false,
      "stimulus_html": "",
      "stem_html": "The second and third steps in osazone formation are tautomerization of the phenylhydrazone to give an enol, followed by elimination of aniline to give a keto imine. Draw the structures of both the enol tautomer and the keto imine.",
      "answers": [],
      "hints": [],
      "formats": [
        "free-response"
      ],
      "combo_choices": []
    },
    {
      "id": 358834,
      "is_answer_order_important": false,
      "stimulus_html": "",
      "stem_html": "The final step is reaction of the keto imine with 2 equivalents of phenylhydrazine to yield the osazone plus ammonia. Propose a mechanism for this step.",
      "answers": [],
      "hints": [],
      "formats": [
        "free-response"
      ],
      "combo_choices": []
    }
  ],
